               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Qāz̤ī ibn Kāshif al-Dīn Muḥammad</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2004002232 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111617 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007008640 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85132924" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_822B-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled Shīʿī doctrinal treatise on contemporary knowledge of medical benefits and preparation methods for chūb-i Chīnī or Chinese root (Smilax china), qahvah or coffee, and chāy or tea, by <persName key="viaf_126146094135600330405" role="aut">Mīrzā Qāz̤ī Muḥammad ibn Kāshif al-Dīn Muḥammad</persName> (d. 1075/1664-5), the latter being physician to <persName key="viaf_77109363" role="oth">Shāh ʿAbbās [I]</persName> (d. 1038/1629), to whom the work is dedicated. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author held the position of Shaykh al-Islām of Iṣfahān, the shah’s cosmopolitan capital city. As a result, the work interestingly references the generalised attitudes of European physicians on the subject. 
</p>
                        <p>The work was written at speed in Persian for the benefit of commoners and élites, for stewards (ghulāmān) and the partisans or Shīʿiyān of <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="oth">Imām ʿAlī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists of three bāb further subdivided into faṣl, with each bāb dealing with the three ingredients individually from a staunchly pro-Shīʿī perspective. 
</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 35v): completed by Ḥakīm ʿAbd Allāh, who collated his copy with the author’s manuscript; not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal naskh, with shikastah used in the colophon and annotations. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections by multiple hands in the margin. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original covers. 
</p>
                        <p>Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on regulations for court martial); watermarked (Britannia/Minerva seated in crowned oval frame; not dated); labels, torn and stained.
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; water stains, wormholes, later repairs, cropped. 
</p>
                     </note>
